name: Ians
description:
This canyon is described in limited detail in Canyons Near Sydney by Rick Jamieson. Help the Australian canyoning community by contributing track notes to ropewiki.com

The correct name is Jan's Canyon.

Approach

Descent

Exit

Red tape

Beta sites

Trip reports and media

Background

The correct name is Jan's canyon (possibly named for Jan Mohandas?). The canyon was added to Rick Jamieson's 5th edition guidebook with a grid reference. A number of wilderness canyons were added to this edition, presumably after a sketch map was shared with the author, and presumably that was a piece of paper that had been photo-copied several times and was difficult to read. Rick Jamieson must have interpreted the word as Ian's rather than Jan's.
